    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.77-78_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">7<del>8</del><add>7</add></fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">MISS FLORENCE E. BOEHMER
                        <lb/>
                    P. O. BOX 156
                        <lb/>
                    BRANSON, MISSOURI</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>May 9, 1958</dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt and Alice,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Just by chance, I saw Mrs. <unclear>Cantwell</unclear> downtown in Branson a few days ago, and learned from her of Mrs. Neihardt's death. Somehow, I failed to see the notice in the Branson paper. You may not know that I am living on the campus at <unclear><hi rend="caps">S.F.O.</hi></unclear></p>
                
                <p>There is nothing I can say to you except that your sorrow is mine too. Over the years I've planned to <unclear>get to</unclear> Columbia for a visit. Now I can't imagine the Neihardt home without Mona in it. All the happy times I spent with all of you in your Branson come keep coming back to me, always with her as the warm center of the happiness. Life brings its chagnes &#8212; some of them happy; some sad; some of them, like death, hard to accept, even
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.77-78_0002"/>
                
                    though we know that it must come.</p>
                    
                <p>You, being the wonderful people you are, will meet this sorrow and become the richer for it. But I just keep wishing &#8212; pointlessly &#8212; that you did not have to.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Love,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Florence Boehmer</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <note type="curatorial"><hi rend="caps">JOHN G. NEIHARDT CENTER</hi></note>
                
            </div1>
            
            
